Records are usually removed within 3 months of an insolvency case ending. To correct an error contact the office that dealt with your bankruptcy. 

###Registers for Scotland and Northern Ireland 
+ [Search Scotland’s insolvency register](http://roi.aib.gov.uk/roi/ "The insolvency register for Scotland"){:rel="external"}  
+ [Search Northern Ireland’s insolvency register](http://www.detini.gov.uk/deti-insolvency-index.htm/ "The insolvency register for Northern Ireland"){:rel="external"}  

###Disqualified directors and insolvent companies 
To get details about disqualified directors and insolvent companies, use these registers:

+ [Search for disqualified directors](http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/ddir/ "Search for disqualified directors"){:rel="external"}
+ [Search for insolvent companies](http://wck2.companieshouse.gov.uk/ "Search for insolvent companies"){:rel="external"}
